I"{<h1 id="how-to-set-refund-policy">How to set refund policy?</h1>

<p>Refund policy will help attendees to be aware about what involved when they ask for a refund after purchasing a ticket. In order to set refund policy, please follow these steps:</p>

<h2 id="step-1-log-in">Step 1: Log in</h2>
<p>Log into your Eventyay account by using your account name and password.</p>

<p><img src="/images/login_box_new.png" alt="Set refund policy" /></p>

<h2 id="step-2-manage-event">Step 2: Manage event</h2>

<p>On the top right hand corner, on the drop down menu, click then select <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">manage event</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-set-refund-policy-2.png" alt="Set refund policy" /></p>

<h2 id="step-3-event-management">Step 3: Event management</h2>

<p>Choose the event to which you want to add <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Refund Policy</code>, click <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">edit</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-set-refund-policy-3.png" alt="Set refund policy" /></p>

<p>You will then be at the main <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Event Editing</code> page, the next step is to choose <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">additional info</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-set-refund-policy-4.png" alt="Set refund policy" /></p>

<p>Scroll down, you will immediately see <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">refund policy</code> box, then just put your information into the box, after that, click save.</p>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-set-refund-policy-5.png" alt="Set refund policy" /></p>
:ET